    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Weapons comprising thin, razor-edged rings of flat steel; as traditionally used by Sikhs. Primarily used as a throwing weapon, but can also be used hand-to-hand. For symbols of the wheel of the law or the symbol of dharma, see "chakras (motifs)." </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
